        {
          "id": "e5d2752069c1_2",
          "href": null,
          "name": "fb57",
          "text": "The following is a transcript of an interview I gave at the Goethe Institute in Sao Paulo on the day of the book launch of ‘Designing Regenerative Cultures’ — published in Brazil as ‘Design de Culturas Regenerativas’ by Editora Bambual:",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 215,
              "href": "https://bambualeditora.com.br/p/design-de-culturas-regenerativas/",
              "rel": "noopener",
              "start": 183,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "e5d2752069c1_3",
          "href": null,
          "name": "eeb3",
          "text": "We live in a time when if we just look at the hard science of climate change we could despair and say maybe it is already too late. But I don’t think that is a way to live into the future. We need to now work miracles because what is likely is unthinkable and unconscionable. We really need to make the impossible happen.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "BQ"
        },
        {
          "id": "e5d2752069c1_4",
          "href": null,
          "name": "538f",
          "text": "Regenerative design — creating regenerative cultures — is about building the capacity of people in place to respond to transformation and change in ways that create a healthier, more vibrant, more vital system that can move on into the future.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "BQ"
        },
        {
          "id": "e5d2752069c1_5",
          "href": null,
          "name": "e1e5",
          "text": "So regenerative cultures will look different in every place. They are expressions that come out of the story of place and the potential that each place has — socially, economically and ecologically. The core element is basically to work with people and build their capacity to manifest that potential.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 241,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 237,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "BQ"
        },
        {
          "id": "e5d2752069c1_6",
          "href": null,
          "name": "3033",
          "text": "We are really in a key point in human history. If we don’t take this window of opportunity of the next two, three, four, maybe five years and begin a long journey of redesigning the human presence on Earth — the human impact on Earth from being degenerative and exploitative to being regenerative and collaborative — then there might not be a future for our species on this planet. So this is literally about human survival.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "BQ"
        },
        {
          "id": "e5d2752069c1_7",
          "href": null,
          "name": "cf7c",
          "text": "I am choosing to be hopeful! I could be distraught and say we don’t have a future but that is not a way to live into the future. I feel that we are at a point of inflection. The planetary immune response is kicking in (Paul Hawken spoke about this in ‘Blessed Unrest’). Life wants to continue. We can achieve this — through us, human beings moving into this regenerative design frame and becoming part of the reGeneration rising — there is still a chance that we can make it. But we have to start today!",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "BQ"
        },
        {
          "id": "e5d2752069c1_8",
          "href": null,
          "name": "8ac0",
          "text": "",
